rmal switching with linear dimming the ballast ics integrate more functions including security protection apfc v halfbridge highside driver and support for multilamp applications the pt and pt high power led driver ics are intended for low voltage led lighting applications such as decorative and emergency lighting each ic provides protection functions and is housed in a small size package sot pt integrates a va mos switch while the pt integrates a va mos switch for high voltage led lighting applications such as home and office lighting ptc’s pt and pt ics feature low startup current and low standby power dissipation the pt integrates a singlestage pfc boostbuck topology which brings a normal led driver circuit’s pf up to more than  the pt operates in hysteretic pfm control mode this architecture enables high accuracy led current control without the need for highside current sensing or the inclusion of any closedloop controllers its hysteretic control method can achieve both good line regulation as well as load regulation in addition the pt provides a softstart feature for car led lighting the pt high power led driver ic integrates a vma mos switch and various protection functions operation at mhz frequency prevents unwanted interference to radio frequency circuitry the pt pt  and pt are intended for led backlighting applications the pt supports channel led drivers the pt supports channel led drivers and the pt supports channel led drivers their peak currents may reach ma ma and ma respectively per channel the pt is a channel constant current driver ic suitable for led billboard applications the pt includes a serial buffer for data latch function and its output pins are guaranteed capable of supporting voltages up to v with v led voltage supply its output can cascade  to  leds the pt can control led luminance not only by current magnitude but also by pwm cycling rate its output pwm pulse width may be as low as ns which can satisfy the high speed pwm demands for controlling luminance and hue ptc is looking forward to your visit to booth no  about ptc ptc has utilized its core technical expertise and experience to successfully develop a series of energysaving led driver and dimming controller lighting solutions for applications including billboards dimming fluorescent tubes way cfl led backlighting decorative lighting and automotive interior led lighting ptc is a reliable partner for your future lighting solution needs go to top low power consumption uhf ookask superheterodyne receiver and transmitternew ic designs  low power consumption uhf ookask superheterodyne receiver and transmitterptc will launch pt low power consumption uhf ookask superheterodyne receiver pt low voltage uhf ookaskfsk transmitter and pt low voltage uhf ookask transmitter the pt is an enhanced version of the pt uhf receiver ic the original pt relied a saw resonator to form the local oscillator and can operate over the frequency range from mhz to mhz while requiring few external components the new pt offers significant improvements the pt reduces the if bandwidth to khz which helps to increase interferer immunity as well as improve receiver sensitivity the pt lo spur level is also reduced enabling easier compliance to rf leakage standards in addition the pt turnon time is reduced making the pt wellsuited for customers who require low latency powersaving mode operation the ptpt transmitter ics both utilize a crystal oscillatorbased pll topology in order to achieve the lowest frequency offset in the mhz to mhz frequency band the ptpt can achieve dbm output power using a v supply voltage the pt pt also require the fewest external components to implement a fullyfunctional uhf transmitter compared with other competitors on the market helping to reduce the size of the pcb real estate required about ptc ptc has accumulated more than  years of experience in the design of analog and digital ics ptcs main products are multimedia audio controller ics display driver ics